#Fragment Britannia, Local, Britannia_Moonglow {
  #Sophistication High {
    #Key "*zoo*"{
      "We closely examine everything, both natural and arcane. The zoo that is to the south of Moonglow provides much materials for the study of animal lore.",
      "We are too busy to wander through the wilderness to view animals in their native habitat. The zoo to the south of Moonglow provides us with much information on the natural fauna.",
      "If it were not for the zoo in southern Moonglow, the mages would have to trek into the wilds to view these humble creatures ... and grass stains make for angry apprentices."
}
    #Key "*graveyard*" "*cemetery*" {
      "Moonglow's graveyard is just north of the zoo. It is the way of things that everyone, even mages, must return to the natural cycle.",
      "The cemetery is found to the south of the city. It is a small one, but strikingly serene.",
      "Our graves are located to the south of the city. There are not many, for when magical research goes awry, there is usually not enough left to intern ...."
}
    #Key "*mag*guild*"{
      "Indeed, Moonglow has several Mages' Guilds. Three in fact. One to the south, one to the east and one to the north.",
      "The three Mages' Guilds can be found scattered about the city's skirts. If thou hast questions concerning quests or other such magic subjects, they are a good place to begin asking questions.",
       "The Mages' Guilds are places those learned in the magic arts gather. If thou hast questions, any of the three are equally knowledgeable. At least two are within easy distance of a teleporter."
}
    #Key "*apprentice*"{
      "Each Mages' Guild has an assigned apprentice living nearby.",
      "There is one apprentice for each Mages' Guild. Therefore, one is to be found near the northern Guild, one near the southern Guild, and one to the east.",
      "Do not be shy of approaching the mages' apprentices. They live near the Mages' Guilds. Apprentices are busy, but rarely so involved as to be unhelpful."
}
    #Key "*professor*" "*mag*teacher*" "*teach*mag*" "*mage*"{
      "Moonglow is full of master mages. Perhaps more than half a dozen, and they can all answer knowledgeably about arcane matters. I'd give thee directions, but they move about throughout the day.",
      "If thou hast a question concerning magic, find a master mage - a professor at the Lycaeum, for instance. They can be touchy at home, but are usually affable during class hours.",
      "Master mages are usually professors at the Lycaeum. They can be found there, or in their homes, or sometimes about the streets of Moonglow. They are usually willing to answer questions."
}
    #Key "*teleporter*"{
      "Moonglow is a grand, vast city, and 'twould be problematic to walk from hither to yon all day. We've four teleporter locations, not counting the one in the center of the city.",
      "Teleporters? Well, there's one near the Lycaeum, of course, one by the zoo, one near the eastern residence section, and one near the northern houses.",
      "We've put a teleporter at each of the far flung edges of town: zoo and Lycaeum, and then the two residential areas."
}
    #Key "*telescope*"{
      "Moonglow got its start, thou knowest, by studying the moons' manipulation of the ether. Our telescope furthers our education about the sky. If thou wishes to see it, head to the easternmost of the city.",
      "Thou canst guess from our city's name that our scholars are intrigued by celestial objects. In the eastern part of the city, near the shore, we have the realms' largest eyeglass pointed at the sky.",
      "There are certainly some schools of magic that ignore the heaven's influence, but in Moonglow it is studied intensely. Our telescope was custom made to scry for those things of most interest to mages."
}
    #Key "*gadget*"{
      "Moonglow is not restricted to the study of magic. We have one of the Gadgeteers' Guilds in the heart of the city.",
      "If thou art interested in finding the Gadgeteers' Guild, look in the main part of the city, toward the southeast.",
      "The Gadgeteers' Guild is in the heart of the city, to the southeast of the teleporters."
}
    #Key "*town hall*" "*city hall*" {
      "If thou'rt looking for the town hall, look to the southwest corner of the heart of Moonglow.",
      "Town hall is  a short walk southwest of the main teleporters.",
      "Town hall is in the city proper, just south of the butcher and herbalist's shops."
}
    #Key "*provisioner*" "*supplies*"{
      "The best place in Moonglow to buy supplies would be at the provisioner's shop, just south of the docks.",
      "I buy my supplies at the provisioner's shop. Thou'lt find him betwixt the baker and tailor.",
      "If thou'rt looking to buy supplies, look around the north part of the commercial section of Moonglow. The provisioner is north of the woodcrafter."
}
    #Key "*wood*er*"{
      "We have an excellent woodcrafter in Moonglow, just south of the provisioner's shop. The skill of the craft is no doubt influenced by the nearby Art Guild.",
      "We do indeed have a woodcrafter. Look between the provisioner and the reagent store.",
      "Thou should stop and take a look at the woodcarver's wares. Thou'lt find the store just north and a bit west from the main teleporter location. The skill and detail work are, I think, second to none."
}
    #Key "*tailor*"{
      "Our tailor has a central location, just across the street from the provisioner.",
      "If thou hast a need for new garb, thou'lt find our tailor in the center portion of Moonglow, just west of the inn.",
      "If thou'rt looking for Moonglow's tailor, find the commercial section and look to its southern edge. There thou'lt find what thou'rt looking for."
}
    #Key "*meat*" "*butcher*"{
      "The town's meat is supplied mostly by the one butcher. Look one door to the north of town hall.",
      "The butcher is across the street from the herbalist. If thou'rt lost, both meat and herbs are to the west of the central teleporters.",
      "The butcher has set up shop next door to the armoury. They are both on the western side of the commercial district."
}
    #Key "*armour*"{
      "Fine armour can be had from the armoury in the center of town. Look to the west of Moonglow, to one side of the street that leads west out of town.",
      "The armourer is neighbor to the healer. They have a friendly rivalry, and jest about which service does a soldier more good.",
      "Thou canst find an armourer in the center of Moonglow. For all this is a city of study and research, the armourer's old fashioned methods still bring a decent living."
}
    #Key "*herb*"{
      "Herbs can be found in the city, west and south of the teleporters.",
      "There is an herbalist in the city proper, in case thou'rt interested in the natural arts. The store is frequented most often by mages who dabble in the gentler of magics.",
      "The herbalist is found but one door south of the shop of reagents. Theirs customers are similar, but their businesses do not conflict as often as thou might suspect."
}
    #Key "*reagent*"{
      "Reagents are quite in demand in Moonglow. There is a store devoted to their sale, close by the teleporters.",
      "Thou won't be surprised to find that there is a brisk trade in reagents hereabouts. The best shop is in town, between the woodcrafter's shop and the herb store.",
      "Reagents can usually be found in the wild, but most prefer the more civilized method of garnering such things ... going to a store and purchasing them. Look east of the armoury for reagent supplies."
}
    #Key "*healer*"{
      "Indeed, our graveyard would be a good deal larger were it not for the skilled hands of our healer. If thou knowest the road that leads out of Moonglow, the healer is the last door on the northern side.",
      "Our healer is in the central part of Moonglow, on the far western side. It is but two doors away from the teleporters, and that's a good thing, I promise.",
      "If thou'rt wounded, see the healer in town. The healer is betwixt the baker and the armoury, just west of the woodcarver."
}
    #Key "*baker*"{
      "All manner of baked goods can be found just south of the docks.",
      "Someone once said: cooking 'tis an art, baking 'tis a science. Rumor has it our baker was once a research mage, and certainly the pastries seem magical indeed!",
      "The baker is but one door west of the provisioner, up on the northern side of Moonglow's central district."
}
    #Key "*docks*"{
      "The docks are easy enough to get to ... they are north of the city proper, and in betwixt the two 'prongs' that extend north into the sea.",
      "The docks are near Moonglow's commercial district, a bit to the north of the baker and provisioner.",
      "If thou canst find the central teleporters, just head north and west to find the docks."
}
    #Key "* inn*"{
      "The city's inn is in the central area, a bit south and east of the tailor.",
      "The inn is east a ways from the docks, a bit south. If thou sees the Artists' Guild, thou art too far east. If thou finds the scholar mage's place, thou art too far south.",
      "The inn is across the street from the tailor, and just next door to the fruit shop."
}
    #Key "*mage*"{
      "The closest thing we have to a common mage's shop is near the center of town, across the street from the woodcrafter's.",
      "We have a mage who deals in potions and other such things. Look a bit south of the tailor, just to the northeast of the teleporters.",
      "There is much magic in Moonglow, but most of it is locked within the scholars' heads. For magic more useful
to a layman, visit the mage's shop, north and east of the teleporters.",
      "If thou'rt interested in potions, the mage's shop is near the tailor is best. If thou'rt after lessons, look to the scholar."
}
    #Key "*art*guild*"{
      "We find that art and science are closely tied together. Moonglow would be a pale shadow without the artist population. Their guild is northeast of the commercial area, east of the inn.",
      "The artists meet at their hall to the northeast of central Moonglow. It is at the base of the northeastern
peninsula. The artists live near there.",
      "The artists live near their guildhall. If thou'rt interested in visiting Moonglow's bastion of the finer arts, look to the east of the main town area. The artists are close by where the road turns northward."
}
    #Key "*fruit*" "*food*" "*produce*" "*farm*"{
      "Fresh fruit can be had at a humble store near the center of town. It is just south of the inn, if thou'rt interested.",
      "We do not do much of our own farming, here in Moonglow. Truth be told, I don't know if that's due to soil or lack of interest. Imported produce is sold from a small store just east of the mage's shop.",
      "The way mages will neglect their meals when researching, it is a wonder that the produce shop stays open at all. If thou hast found the scholar's place in town, look just north of there for our fresh produce."
}
    #Key "*scholar*"{
      "If thou'rt interested in learning a bit about the ways of magic, the scholar is who thou needst see. Thou'lt find the place just east of the teleporters.",
      "Mages will give advice, and the mage's shop will sell potions, but for someone to teach thee a thing or two about the mystic arts, look to the shop just east of the teleporters.",
      "North of the Gadgeteers' Guild is a mage scholar who will teach travelers his lore, regardless of whether they attend the Lycaeum."
}
    #Key "*mag*student*"{
      "Students of the arcane arts travel from all over the realm to study in Moonglow. Whilst they are here, they
live in the dormitory north of the Lycaeum.",
      "All are students, friend, of different subjects, and in different ways. Some students of magic come here, to
study at the Lycaeum.",
      "To be a student here is not so much a matter of classes and lectures, but an attitude. Students should not so much study, but be curious, observe and absorb."
}
    #Key "*lycaeum"{
      "Moonglow was founded by Lord British to be a research colony. The Lycaeum is where the research takes place. Nearly all new magic in Britain comes from that building on the northwest peninsula.",
      "Nearly every form of magic, be it sorcery or enchantment is studied at the Lycaeum. It is famous the world over. To find it, just head west and north from central Moonglow.",
      "The Lycaeum is west and north of the docks. The building is enormous, thou cannot miss it."
}
#Key "*britain*" "*capital*" {
      "Britain thou'rt askin' about? 'Tis the biggest city in the land",
      "Britain? I went there once. 'Tis over by the eastern shore, at the mouth of a great river. That's where Lord British holds his court, but I saw him not even once.",
      "Britain? 'Tis the capital of the whole world, o'course. Sits on the shore of Britanny Bay way off to the west.",
