      "A place of magic, is Britain. Some say they invent a new spell every day. Of course, nothing like our own studies ....",
      "They're fair folk in Britain, mainly. A bit overloud for my tastes.",
      "Britain was the first place where people are judged according to their own accomplishments, not their fathers'. 'Tis a tricky thing to make work, I'd imagine.",
      "'Tis  the very center upon which all ill-natured rogues converge. They seek to destroy what they cannot understand.",
      "Britain? Seems a nice place, from what all I've heard.",
      "Britain? Been once. Quite big."
    }
