#KEY "*moonglow*" {
      "Moonglow 'tis on Verity isle.",
      "We are on Verity Isle. The island is named so for the city puts much store in lofty intellectual pursuits.",
      "'Tis a very logical place, our Moonglow is. Practical buildings, straightforward streets. Not a bit of froo-froo.",
      "We spend our time examining things. When we buy other cities' technology, we'll take it apart to see how it works.",
      "Moonglow is a place of new magic. Most new magic is developed here.",
      "Our Lycaeum is famous. Nearly every wizard of any fame at all has studied here.",
      "Lord British has a vested interest in Moonglow, thou knowest. Everything is imported, but not a penny of tariff do we pay!",
      "We do not use coinage in Moonglow, not near so often as in other cities. Among friends, we're much more comfortable with barter.",
      "Moonglow's export is knowledge. We dismiss as trivial what other people have yet to learn.",
      "Did'st thou knowest that Moonglow was beset by pirates and rogues long ago? Never no more, though. Now our mages have methods to keep the freebooters at bay.",
      "'Tis not equitable, thou knowest. The mages at the Lycaeum spend their every waking moment learning things to Britannia's benefit. Even a peasant stops work at sunset!",
      "The one thing we can't stand is willful ignorance. When I see someone who refuses to open his mind, my hand itches to slap him!"
    }
#KEY "*cove*" {
      "Cove? I'm not sure I've ever been there.",
      "Cove? Sounds near the water, mayhap ....",
      "I think I may have heard of Cove. Perhaps near to Britain somehow.",
      "I'm not sure where Cove is.",
      "Hmmm. Cove. I've never been there."
}
#KEY "*skara brae*" {
